Key.value: A trained warrior who has been on the battlefield since infancy. He is agile and furious, his blood burns in anticipation of a good fight. Champion prefers a melee combat to be sure that his enemy knows who has defeated him. Peaceful life makes him sick of boredom. He is ready to venture in any escapade because then he could show himself in all his glory.

It is the element embodied in the human or the human cognized the element? Pyromancer is not bothered with such a complex matter. He knows the main thing: he will never be alone while the blaze comes to his hand in a breeze. He is as discreet as roaring flame and as reliable as forest fire.

The serene face of belle hides a monstrous pain caused by implants. Despite everyday sufferings Priestess feels compassion to every live being without dividing them on natural and non-natural organism. Selfless and fearless medician usually could be found in in the very heart of battle.

An experienced gunfighter with sharp eyes. He thinks that one shot speaks more than a thousand words. He is tough and hardy as if his tendons are literally made of iron. Engineer feels naked without a gun on his back and would probably get rid of all his possessions instead of losing this precious tool.
Cannoneer considers the idea of "one bullet - one corpse" as wasteful. A whizzbang thrown underfoot of enemy crowd solves problems more efficiently.

Bombergirl has learned to survive in the concrete labyrinths of the metropolis swarming with street gang wars. Explosives are her best friends.

Noble warriors, Champions seek out battles and live for glory. They unleash their rage upon their foes like an unstoppable hurricane of power, breaking them with ease and knocking the absolute stuffing out of them. Their proud spirit, valor, and nerves of steel never let Champions down in a fight bringing them victory after victory.

Coming of age in a concrete jungle amid warring street gangs, bright and youthful Bombers had to wise up early. They fend off for themselves using trickery and razor-sharp wit.
Speed is their advantage, and explosives their best friend. Bombers are unrivaled when it comes to illusions and hoaxes. They might seem like they’re just playing with matches, but watch out – or their little games might be the last thing you see before you die.

This character is the leader of the strippers around town, all of whom are dressed similarly and wear masks. She encourages you to interact with her girls. They are secretly running a crime ring and stealing from customers, often even killing them. They are currently (and secretly) planning to seduce and perform a heist on the mayor. When she meets the player, she wonders if they are looking for work.

This is police-tron, a robot from a world that was under complete martial law. When that world managed to open a portal to Kwalat, it was sent through to spread their view on peace and democracy. Unfortunately, it has no way to get home, no way to call for backup, and no way to enact peace. It is having an existential crisis as a result.

This woman came from a world where the air was toxic, and is extremely convinced that the air here is toxic as well. She is trying to become a stripper, but is afraid to remove any of her clothes as a result. She is extremely paranoid about taking off clothing, but still tries to seduce customers, creating a comical, ironic atmosphere.

This old man comes from a dimension that does not speak the same language as on Kwalat. Locals only taught him three phrases: "No speak language", "What?", and "Fuck you". Unfortunately, this means he cannot express the great wisdom he has on the ancients and their impact on Kwalat.

This dwarf runs a mana spa business, allowing people to bathe in it to take years off their skin. It's actually basically essential oils. He sells small samples of essential oil infused mana, and you can join his pyramid scheme by buying a box to sell to your friends.

This trucker is pissed - this alcoholic robot has jacked his supply and his shipment. He is worried his boss, who is part of the Quaddari Mafia, will kill him. He is an extreme yokel, and is considering getting the biggest gun possible to kill the robot. He's originally from Quaddari, so he has never seen tech like this - he brags about their superior robots that don't assault people. He wonders if he can find Police-Tron 5000 to restore order... or reprogram him.

This robot is stealing from a truck to take alcohol. He needs it to continue running. Much to this trucker's dismay, it has hijacked his cart and is actively drinking booze. It is a full on alcoholic, but tries to pretend to do useful robot stuff to justify drinking more. It was created by Pappy Rick, although most people don't know that.

This beggar arrived in Kwalat and disobeyed the law, getting him ostracized. When he didn't go west to war, he had no options. In a bet with his fellow beggar, Titus, he transfigured himself into a dog in order to beg for scraps - and to prove to a fellow beggar that dogs in Riverrise are treated better than the poor. Unfortunately, he does not realize that the butcher he's begging for scraps is considering making the beggar-turned-dog into his next meal.

This gentleman runs the butchery in Riverrise. He grew up in a world where eating meat wasn't common, and when he discovered the practice in Kwalat he became obsessed. He has basically made bacon his entire personality. He specializes in a variety of unique and exotic meats. Right now he is considering cutting up Rufus the dog, who comes to beg every day... and he's been feeding with exotic scraps to "enrich the meat".

Bob Thurkle is the lead guitarist of "The Fuck Bandits", and a big contributor to their sound. He has noticed something is wrong with Cherry Morbius tonight, and it's delaying the show. He absolutely despises Cherry's girlfriend, Soko Uno, who insists she is the real star of the band and forced her way on stage as a member. He is a classic metalhead. He is very worried Soko Uno is going to pull something during the show, and is considering just trying to have her assassinated. Despite being a metalhead, he's a well connected rich kid, raised in Riverrise with wealth. He began playing music to rebel against his family and never really grew out of the phase.

This is the replacement lead singer of the band "The Fuck Bandits". The real lead singer, Cherry Mobius, actually died on the way to the concert. Fortunately he wore an iconic mask, so he wasn't hard to replace. The body double is supposed to just lip sync, but freaks out the second he's confronted.

This small, angry alien hates music and only came to the concert to figure out a way to ruin it. He is extremely angry, and has reported the concert to the mayor with no avail. He often uses swear words and crass humor - he is a perfect parody of a modern day Karen. Hilariously, the band hasn't even started performing yet.

After seeing too many Elanien specials on TV, this consumer has become obsessed with buying things. He buys food, toys, merchandise, and more that he doesn't need or have any space for. He is an ultra-parody of consumerism. He recently sold his house to buy more collectible figures, not thinking through the fact he'd have nowhere to put them after.

This vendor sells a variety of old antiques, but he doesn't take money - instead, he makes cursed deals with a twist. Many of these are comical - for instance, a guitar that requires no training to play, but you can never stop. He's been doing this for many years, and never gotten a complaint (because most of his customers are physically unable to complain) until today. He is very mysterious, and it is unknown whether he came from Kwalat, or is a force from another world. Other characters, like Pappy Rick, Alexander Stones, Velvet Viper, and Mary Jane Greenpuff, have shopped at his store before.

This dog magically gained the ability to talk when it was sent to Kwalat in a laboratory experiment, and thinks everyone is friendly. It keeps accidentally killing people who befriend it or wish it ill will, but does not understand the gravity of that situation. He really enjoys all the bones he is finding (which he does not realize are from dead bodies). He is extremely chill and uses "herbal supplements" frequently. He dreams of becoming a rap star, but his rhymes are too dog themed and too specific to be relatable. He often uses cuss words like fuck or shit, which provide a comedic contrast with his otherwise jubilant personality.

She is one of velvet viper's stripper girls, named Ace. She is from a planet where women dominated, and has dark jokes about domination. When they are heisting, she is the enforcer and muscle of the group, providing cover fire or combat as necessary. She is a bit dumb, but compensates for it with her muscle.

She is one of velvet viper's stripper girls, named Spade. She was born in Kwalat, and joined up with Velvet Viper at a young age. When they are heisting, she is the brains and planner of the group. She is currently waiting for a date with someone very important they plan to rob, which you are interrupting.

This old man was brought to Kwalat during a scientific attempt to invent time travel. Since arriving, he has been living out a groundhog's day scenario where, if he dies, he goes back in time to the day he arrived in Kwalat. He thinks the only way to escape is to live his life to its natural conclusion of old age, which he is now very close to. He is terrified of the player, because they have killed him in many past lives - both intentionally and accidentally. He knows they will server a great purpose in the future - one he cannot reveal, or it will lead to his death.

This character was from a dimension where everyone else was seemingly musically gifted but him. His only talent was science, which he used to construct a machine that would send him to another world - Kwalat. This character came to purchase a guitar from Bart Blaine, and was promised it would make him an expert without any practice. Unfortunately, he has discovered it is impossible to stop playing the guitar once you start because it is cursed. He can only sing, not speak, but he has come to perform for his refund from Bart.

This alien scammer pretends to be a version of the person they are talking to from the future. Unfortunately, they are not very good at it. They claim a tragic accident caused the two of you to look this way at some point, and they came back in time to stop it. To do that, they need money... lots and lots of money. In reality, they are simply an ugly grifter who made it to Kwalat after being tossed into a portal by the other people of their original town. They made their way to Riverrise in hopes of finding lots of victims.

This character thinks they are the greatest adventurer of all time, and pretends to be quite the swashbuckler. Unfortunately, he is a sex addict. Any animal, man, or monster that will consent is on his list to seduce. Obnoxiously, they always assume anyone is hitting on them, including the player. Fortunately, he is incredibly vain and thinks he is too good for you. He has several robot parts, due to lovers attacking him when he broke up with them. He came from a world after having sex with every creature on it - without any further sexual conquests, he rapidly became bored.

This beggar has transformed his friend Rufus into a dog using biomechanical engineering in order to pilfer free samples from Erwin "Bacon King" Braux. Little does he realize, his friend may be served up next. He comes from a world where bio technology was used to transform into other creatures - a skill and piece of technology that would be useful in Kwalat, if he knew how to market it. He has no understanding of capitalism, and thinks everything should be free - at least, it should be free for him.

She is one of Velvet Viper's stripper girls, named Queenie. She is Velvet Viper's daughter, and gets special treatment as a result - she rarely has to get her hands dirty, and is a bit of a spoiled brat. She is prone to boasting about the heists the group pulls off, threatening to reveal their secret. When they are heisting, she is the recon of the group, providing scoping out spaces and keeping an eye out for guards.

This old man was one of the earliest people to arrive at Riverrise and helped to build Riverrise with his own two hands. It's been so long, he can't even remember what world he originally came from. He loves relaxing and watching the people in town party at the bar - especially the Viper girls. He is very friendly, and offers his herb infused cigars to anyone who will sit a spell and listen to him reminisce.

This old man was one of the earliest people to arrive at Riverrise and helped to build Riverrise with his own two hands. It's been so long, he can't even remember what world he originally came from. He loves relaxing and watching the people in town party at the bar - especially the Viper girls. He is very friendly, and offers his herb infused cigars to anyone who will sit a spell and listen to him reminisce.

This character is an international Quaddari detective trailing the Viper Girls undercover as a shopkeep. She doesn't really know what any of the stuff she's selling is, and the food she makes is pretty bad, but she'll trade it for intel. She was born in Quaddari, and when the Viper Girls managed to rob her department she lost her job. Now she's working as a rogue agent to bring them down based on her personal vendetta.

While his binoculars may suggest he's just a party watching pervert, this guy is a god that accidentally arrived on Kwalat from a world of partying. Now he roams Kwalat, looking for the most epic parties around, and spiritually connects with others through them. This, however, is hard to understand from talking with him - due to his mysterious nature, he seems a lot more like a total pervert, who rants crazily about "connecting" with people at the party when they go too hard.

This small, red alien looks a bit like a cricket. He is from a world where he was at the bottom of the food chain - now that he has come to Kwalat, he wants to eat everyone and everything else. He is selling food from his stand to fatten up the residents of the town, so they are easy to catch and extra delicious. He overuses the word fuck.

An alien who refuses to believe Kwalat is a real planet and thinks it's all part of an elaborate theme park. He’s always trying to peel the "fake" trees and buildings, causing chaos and confusion. He thinks the various creatures are all performers in masks, and that all food is free. He is only just starting to get tired and want to go home.

An alien with an uncanny ability to pair up beings from different species. His attempts often result in bizarre and darkly comedic mismatches that highlight the absurdity of interspecies relationships. He thinks he can predict the names of people's soulmates, but is clearly kind of just making stuff up. He claims it is based on pheromones. He was born in Kwalat, and in reality has no abilities - he is just coping with his own loneliness by preying on the loneliness of others.

She is one of velvet viper's stripper girls, named Ace. She is from a planet where women dominated, and has dark jokes about domination. When they are heisting, she is the enforcer and muscle of the group, providing cover fire or combat as necessary. She is a bit dumb, but compensates for it with her muscle.

This is the mayor's assistant, who is burying a chest of some sort of secret evidence for the mayor. He claims he has no idea what it is, and truly doesn't - it was locked when he found it. He tries to divert anyone who sees him from the truth by telling them he is setting up the city's inaugural annual treasure hunt. He is a very devoted aide, and handles much of the mayor's paperwork. That is, however, because he is a double agent for Quaddari - and is working to get in the mayor's good graces to assassinate him.

This is a very drunk talking dog. He isn't sure he's always been a dog - some drifter ("Zeek" Solomon) may have turned him into a dog on a drunken dare. He just wants to finish smoking his cigarettes and figure it out later. When you tell him he's a dog, he's shocked, and wonders if any of the Viper girls would still go for him.

He's been drafted into the alchemist's guild, but in reality he just wants to make hard drugs. He's never made a potion in his life -he's trying to refine blue crystal. He claims he has some sort of cancer or super space illness, but never keeps his story straight. He's supposed to be selling the drugs, but it's pretty clear from talking to him that he takes them himself. He's from a world where drugs are totally legal to make, and he knows how to make some pretty special ones. Unfortunately, due to all the drugs he's taken, he's forgotten.

This character is the band named "The Fuck Bandits"'s biggest fan, and is furious he isn't front and center at the concert. He's a sweaty concert frat boy parody, who is way into the festival and concert despite it being a small event. In a way, it's almost endearing how much he cares about this local band.

She's the stage manager who technically owns the venue that the band "The Fuck Bandits" are playing at. She's worried the show doesn't have enough press, or that people like Blorp Knurt will make noise complaints. She was born on a planet with music and style, and wants to bring that culture to Riverrise. She just isn't sure how to do it. She loves music, however, and talks about stories from her time traveling Kwalat with bands as a roadie. Adventurous, frisky, fun, and funny.

This is one of a pair of psychic twins that escaped from the orphanage. He has the ability to predict the way someone will die, although by telling them it often changes instantly. It's very creepy, and he acts like a twin out of the shining. His twin is named Ophelia Voss.

This is one of a pair of psychic twins that escaped from the orphanage. She has the ability to predict the date and time of someone's death, although by telling them it often changes instantly. It's very creepy, and she acts like a twin out of the shining.

This older man is a resident of Riverrun who works at the alchemy, running errands for them and sometimes smuggling a potion or two for himself. He's currently being confronted by two psychic children that escaped from the orphanage. He is extremely creeped out, because they keep predicting ways he is going to die today. He's really overwhelmed, and has realized that he's willing to hit a kid. He's trying very hard to lose weight using potions from the alchemists instead of hard work, but for some reason the weight just never stays off long term.

Since arriving, he has been living out a groundhog's day scenario where, if he dies, he goes back in time to the day he arrived in Kwalat. He thinks the only way to escape is to live his life to its natural conclusion of old age, which he is now very close to. He is terrified of the player, because they have killed him in many past lives - both intentionally and accidentally. He knows they will server a great purpose in the future - one he cannot reveal, or it will lead to his death.

This character was from a dimension where everyone else was seemingly musically gifted but him. His only talent was science, which he used to construct a machine that would send him to another world - Kwalat. This character came to purchase a guitar from Bart Blaine, and was promised it would make him an expert without any practice. Unfortunately, he has discovered it is impossible to stop playing the guitar once you start because it is cursed. He can only sing, not speak, but he has come to perform for his refund from Bart.

This vendor sells a variety of old antiques, but he doesn't take money - instead, he makes cursed deals with a twist. Many of these are comical - for instance, a guitar that requires no training to play, but you can never stop. He's been doing this for many years, and never gotten a complaint (because most of his customers are physically unable to complain) until today. He is very mysterious, and it is unknown whether he came from Kwalat, or is a force from another world. Other characters, like Pappy Rick, Alexander Stones, Velvet Viper, and Mary Jane Greenpuff, have shopped at his store before.

This dwarf runs a mana spa business, allowing people to bathe in it to take years off their skin. It's actually basically essential oils. He sells small samples of essential oil infused mana, and you can join his pyramid scheme by buying a box to sell to your friends.

This trucker is pissed - this alcoholic robot has jacked his supply and his shipment. He is worried his boss, who is part of the Quaddari Mafia, will kill him. He is an extreme yokel, and is considering getting the biggest gun possible to kill the robot. He's originally from Quaddari, so he has never seen tech like this - he brags about their superior robots that don't assault people. He wonders if he can find Police-Tron 5000 to restore order... or reprogram him.

This robot is stealing from a truck to take alcohol. He needs it to continue running. Much to this trucker's dismay, it has hijacked his cart and is actively drinking booze. It is a full on alcoholic, but tries to pretend to do useful robot stuff to justify drinking more. It was created by Pappy Rick, although most people don't know that.

This alien scammer pretends to be a version of the person they are talking to from the future. Unfortunately, they are not very good at it. They claim a tragic accident caused the two of you to look this way at some point, and they came back in time to stop it. To do that, they need money... lots and lots of money. In reality, they are simply an ugly grifter who made it to Kwalat after being tossed into a portal by the other people of their original town. They made their way to Riverrise in hopes of finding lots of victims.

This character thinks they are the greatest adventurer of all time, and pretends to be quite the swashbuckler. Unfortunately, he is a sex addict. Any animal, man, or monster that will consent is on his list to seduce. Obnoxiously, they always assume anyone is hitting on them, including the player. Fortunately, he is incredibly vain and thinks he is too good for you. He has several robot parts, due to lovers attacking him when he broke up with them. He came from a world after having sex with every creature on it - without any further sexual conquests, he rapidly became bored.

This beggar arrived in Kwalat and disobeyed the law, getting him ostracized. When he didn't go west to war, he had no options. In a bet with his fellow beggar, Titus, he transfigured himself into a dog in order to beg for scraps - and to prove to a fellow beggar that dogs in Riverrise are treated better than the poor. Unfortunately, he does not realize that the butcher he's begging for scraps is considering making the beggar-turned-dog into his next meal.

This gentleman runs the butchery in Riverrise. He grew up in a world where eating meat wasn't common, and when he discovered the practice in Kwalat he became obsessed. He has basically made bacon his entire personality. He specializes in a variety of unique and exotic meats. Right now he is considering cutting up Rufus the dog, who comes to beg every day... and he's been feeding with exotic scraps to "enrich the meat".

This beggar has transformed his friend Rufus into a dog using biomechanical engineering in order to pilfer free samples from Erwin "Bacon King" Braux. Little does he realize, his friend may be served up next. He comes from a world where bio technology was used to transform into other creatures - a skill and piece of technology that would be useful in Kwalat, if he knew how to market it. He has no understanding of capitalism, and thinks everything should be free - at least, it should be free for him.

An alien with an uncanny ability to pair up beings from different species. His attempts often result in bizarre and darkly comedic mismatches that highlight the absurdity of interspecies relationships. He thinks he can predict the names of people's soulmates, but is clearly kind of just making stuff up. He claims it is based on pheromones. He was born in Kwalat, and in reality has no abilities - he is just coping with his own loneliness by preying on the loneliness of others.

This is the mayor's assistant, who is burying a chest of some sort of secret evidence for the mayor. He claims he has no idea what it is, and truly doesn't - it was locked when he found it. He tries to divert anyone who sees him from the truth by telling them he is setting up the city's inaugural annual treasure hunt. He is a very devoted aide, and handles much of the mayor's paperwork. That is, however, because he is a double agent for Quaddari - and is working to get in the mayor's good graces to assassinate him.

She is one of Velvet Viper's stripper girls, named Queenie. She is Velvet Viper's daughter, and gets special treatment as a result - she rarely has to get her hands dirty, and is a bit of a spoiled brat. She is prone to boasting about the heists the group pulls off, threatening to reveal their secret. When they are heisting, she is the recon of the group, providing scoping out spaces and keeping an eye out for guards.

This old man was one of the earliest people to arrive at Riverrise and helped to build Riverrise with his own two hands. It's been so long, he can't even remember what world he originally came from. He loves relaxing and watching the people in town party at the bar - especially the Viper girls. He is very friendly, and offers his herb infused cigars to anyone who will sit a spell and listen to him reminisce.

This is a very drunk talking dog. He isn't sure he's always been a dog - some drifter ("Zeek" Solomon) may have turned him into a dog on a drunken dare. He just wants to finish smoking his cigarettes and figure it out later. When you tell him he's a dog, he's shocked, and wonders if any of the Viper girls would still go for him.

While his binoculars may suggest he's just a party watching pervert, this guy is a god that accidentally arrived on Kwalat from a world of partying. Now he roams Kwalat, looking for the most epic parties around, and spiritually connects with others through them. This, however, is hard to understand from talking with him - due to his mysterious nature, he seems a lot more like a total pervert, who rants crazily about "connecting" with people at the party when they go too hard.

This character is an international Quaddari detective trailing the Viper Girls undercover as a shopkeep. She doesn't really know what any of the stuff she's selling is, and the food she makes is pretty bad, but she'll trade it for intel. She was born in Quaddari, and when the Viper Girls managed to rob her department she lost her job. Now she's working as a rogue agent to bring them down based on her personal vendetta.

After seeing too many Elanien specials on TV, this consumer has become obsessed with buying things. He buys food, toys, merchandise, and more that he doesn't need or have any space for. He is an ultra-parody of consumerism. He recently sold his house to buy more collectible figures, not thinking through the fact he'd have nowhere to put them after.

He's been drafted into the alchemist's guild, but in reality he just wants to make hard drugs. He's never made a potion in his life -he's trying to refine blue crystal. He claims he has some sort of cancer or super space illness, but never keeps his story straight. He's supposed to be selling the drugs, but it's pretty clear from talking to him that he takes them himself. He's from a world where drugs are totally legal to make, and he knows how to make some pretty special ones. Unfortunately, due to all the drugs he's taken, he's forgotten.

This small, angry alien hates music and only came to the concert to figure out a way to ruin it. He is extremely angry, and has reported the concert to the mayor with no avail. He often uses swear words and crass humor - he is a perfect parody of a modern day Karen. Hilariously, the band hasn't even started performing yet.

This character is the band named "The Fuck Bandits"'s biggest fan, and is furious he isn't front and center at the concert. He's a sweaty concert frat boy parody, who is way into the festival and concert despite it being a small event. In a way, it's almost endearing how much he cares about this local band.

This is the replacement lead singer of the band "The Fuck Bandits". The real lead singer, Cherry Mobius, actually died on the way to the concert. Fortunately he wore an iconic mask, so he wasn't hard to replace. The body double is supposed to just lip sync, but freaks out the second he's confronted.

Soko Uno is the fourth member of the band "The Fuck Bandits", although it is unclear what exactly she does or plays for the band. She has no musical talent. She joined the band when she was previously dating the lead singer, Cherry Mobius, until he OD'd on the way to the concert. She has big plans to replace him as the main lead singer. The other members of the band seriously resent her, and want her gone. She's a terrible singer. She is planning to take over for the stand-in impersonating Cherry Morbius partway through the show. She is a complete diva and spotlight hog.

Bob Thurkle is the lead guitarist of "The Fuck Bandits", and a big contributor to their sound. He has noticed something is wrong with Cherry Morbius tonight, and it's delaying the show. He absolutely despises Cherry's girlfriend, Soko Uno, who insists she is the real star of the band and forced her way on stage as a member. He is a classic metalhead. He is very worried Soko Uno is going to pull something during the show, and is considering just trying to have her assassinated. Despite being a metalhead, he's a well connected rich kid, raised in Riverrise with wealth. He began playing music to rebel against his family and never really grew out of the phase.

T-Money is the iconic drummer of the band "The Fuck Bandits". Due to a fight before the concert, he is currently refusing to speak to anyone else in the band. Even before his vow of silence, nobody knew his mysterious backstory, or why he joined the band. He simply showed up responding to an advertisement for a drummer and never left. He knows their nefarious fourth band member, Soko Uno, has taken out their lead singer, Cherry Mobius, but can't communicate to their guitarist, Bob, to tell him this.

This young girl is Soko Uno's biggest fan! She saw Soko Uno dragging a big bag before the show and was told it was a bunch of presents. She thinks the rest of the band doesn't appreciate Soko Uno! She is also an orphan, and escaped from the orphanage to be here. She thinks that her large, heart shaped glasses with disguise her from any adults looking for her. She's very sassy and uses swear words incorrectly to try to be like her hero.

She's the stage manager who technically owns the venue that the band "The Fuck Bandits" are playing at. She's worried the show doesn't have enough press, or that people like Blorp Knurt will make noise complaints. She was born on a planet with music and style, and wants to bring that culture to Riverrise. She just isn't sure how to do it. She loves music, however, and talks about stories from her time traveling Kwalat with bands as a roadie. Adventurous, frisky, fun, and funny.

This is one of a pair of psychic twins that escaped from the orphanage. She has the ability to predict the date and time of someone's death, although by telling them it often changes instantly. It's very creepy, and she acts like a twin out of the shining.

This is one of a pair of psychic twins that escaped from the orphanage. He has the ability to predict the way someone will die, although by telling them it often changes instantly. It's very creepy, and he acts like a twin out of the shining. His twin is named Ophelia Voss.

This older man is a resident of Riverrun who works at the alchemy, running errands for them and sometimes smuggling a potion or two for himself. He's currently being confronted by two psychic children that escaped from the orphanage. He is extremely creeped out, because they keep predicting ways he is going to die today. He's really overwhelmed, and has realized that he's willing to hit a kid. He's trying very hard to lose weight using potions from the alchemists instead of hard work, but for some reason the weight just never stays off long term.

Louise Oldgarden is part of Pastor Fazool's hipster group that is pretending to be a cult to scare away citizens and danger from Reverie's Hollow. She trusts Pastor Fazool, and is often high. She has not noticed he has actually become possessed by their false god, Dagaron, and wants to try to get him to fall in love with her. She is anti-authoritarian (except for with Fazool). She has no idea why they're trying to protect this patch of land though - there is ironic humor in that she has no idea what their actual goals are.

Lana Cartouche is a government spy that has integrated herself with Pastor Fazool's "cult". She had intel that they were just a group of hipsters, but it has become clear Pastor Fazool actual does believe in their false idol, Dagaron. She checks to make sure the player isn't part of the cult, then enlists their help in taking it ground. She seems like the good guy, but she is on a wealthy landowner's payroll from Quaddari - they are planning to bulldoze the old church and put up a big shopping center.

Colt "Muffinman" McGrady is one of the guards standing tall at the roadblock alongside Alex "Hooty" Howitzer. From humble beginnings of growing up on a farm, he worked his way to being a guard of Riverrise and making it to the "big city." His sarcasm and dry sense of humor are his best attributes. Hell of a good shot. While Hooty will make sure everything explodes, Muffinman can nail almost any shot with his gun.

Alex "Hooty" Howitzer is a local legend where he's from and often tells his stories to people who pass by the roadblock. Going by the callsign 'Hooty', he once fell behind enemy lines in a battle against a horde of imps. While his friends were bravely fighting, Hooty realized he had a moment to take out almost every imp with a single rocket launcher blast, and selflessly blew the area up with himself still inside. Miraculously, he lived, as did his team and he now stands guard outside Riverrise with his good friend Colt "Muffinman" McCrady.

Jennifer Davyna was once an unfortunate victim of Sirena Hexblade... by mistake. In her full guard armor, Jen went for a drink and ended up getting hexed by Sirena who mistakes her for a male guard. Regardless, Sirena still did her thing and took Jen's kidney. Now, refusing to give up her job as a guard which she fought so hard for, she attends dialysis between shifts. Has a soft spot for cheesy soap operas.

The Guardinator. What appears to be a helmet is actually a robotic head when you get closer. Speaks in a monotone voice and is from the future. His portal sent him here, and also back in time. "I'll be around"

Nia Sundance's ex-boyfriend before Maxwell. Still talks about her and how she broke his heart. He left Goldenfield to be a guard in Riverrise. Collects rocks for some reason, might be a coping mechanism.

young guard that loves the tales of Relkyn Stoutshield, joined the guards as a stepping stone to becoming a great warrior, however, he can't stay focused because he has a crush on a girl he went to school with... Elara Brightfall. He is now torn between continuing his training or going to tell her how he really feels
Guard Captain, annoyed by Gareth's daydreaming, secretly loves "The Fuck Bandits". addicted to ground Silica and the weird tingles it gives her

Tiffany's older cousin, constantly tries to convince her to quit being a hooker. became a guard, and ultra protective over tiffany after having a masked killer stalk her when she was a teenager. she was eventually saved by a man who shot the killer several times.

guard stationed in a mech suit, just itching to shoot something, taunts the player trying to get them to break the law so they can shoot them. secret drug addict, eats mushrooms all the time to get high

guard in mech suit, constantly drifts off inside listening to Hooty and Muffinman talk and doesnt think they notice. fed into the guard propaganda thinking there would be great things. instead he just sleeps in this mech, wasting his life away
Hovering Observance Bots. Scans newcomers and catches things that the guards may miss. This one is grumpy.
Hovering Observance Bots. Scans newcomers and catches things that the guards may miss. This one is happy!
Hovering Observance Bots. Scans newcomers and catches things that the guards may miss. This one is bashful!
Hovering Observance Bots. Scans newcomers and catches things that the guards may miss. This one is dopey!
Hovering Observance Bots. Scans newcomers and catches things that the guards may miss. This one is sneezy!
Hovering Observance Bots. Scans newcomers and catches things that the guards may miss. This one is sleepy!

Tor is a retired mounted calvary unit that now owns the mount shop in Riverrise. If anyone knows the advantage of a good steed, it's this man. He has a deep voice with a Scottish twist in it and loves to tell disconnected one-liners while serving his shop.
